<item>
            <title>[WICKET-5469] ModalWindow unload warning always displayed (even if window is closed)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-5469</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fix applied for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4909&quot; title=&quot;ModalWindow overwrites window.onbeforeunload&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4909&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4909&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; seems to be bad:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there&apos;s a ModalWindow with showUnloadConfirmation == true (java) and window.onbeforeunload == null (javascript), the warning message (&apos;Reloading this page will cause the modal window to disappear&apos;) is always displayed, even if the ModalWindow was closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4909&quot; title=&quot;ModalWindow overwrites window.onbeforeunload&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4909&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4909&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should probably take the showUnloadConfirmation flag into account.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12688247">WICKET-5469</key>
            <summary>ModalWindow unload warning always displayed (even if window is closed)</summary>
